<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1426,1595]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,1462,1487]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species belongs in the 
<taxonomicName box="[793,868,1463,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parcus">
<emphasis box="[793,868,1463,1486]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">parcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The male can be separated from all other members of the genus by the needle shaped median volsella with basal seta.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
